The article discusses the celebration of Greek Independence Day and the historical ties between Greece and the United States. It highlights the shared values of democracy and the support given by the United States to Greece during its fight for independence from the Ottoman Empire and in World War II. The article emphasizes the strong alliance between the two countries today, with cooperation in various areas such as climate, trade, and pandemic response. It also acknowledges the contributions of Greek Americans in strengthening the partnership between Greece and the United States. The article concludes with President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaiming March 25, 2023, as Greek Independence Day and calling upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.